==Introduction==
The '''Option Type''' represents a properties which values need to be limited to ones from the allowed list of items.

The Wiki Automation Tool supports editing, viewing and searching on the Option properties.


==Definition==

The Option Property extends a common definition of the [[Help:Property|Property Definition]] with the following elements:

<pre>

<concept name="{CONCEPT NAME}">
  <structure>

    <property name="{PROPERTY NAME}" editField="{EDIT FIELD}" format="{FORMAT}"/>

  </structure>
</concept>


<properties>

  <property name="{PROPERTY NAME}"...>
    <values default="{DEFAULT VALUE}">
      <value name="{VALUE}">{LABEL}</value>
      ...
    </values>
  </property>

</properties>
</pre>

{| class="helptable"
|-
! {PROPERTY NAME}
| A name of the Option property.
|-
! values
| A section which allows to define a list of available items.
|-
! {DEFAULT VALUE}
| A default value for the Option property.
|-
! {VALUE}
| A value of the allowed item.
|-
! {LABEL}
| A label of the allowed item.
|-
! {EDIT FIELD}
| A type of the inout field to be used to select the value. The following values are allowed:
* ''listbox'' (default for: multi-value properties with list of values > 10)
* ''checkboxes'' (default for: multi-value properties with list of values <= 10)
* ''combobox'' (default for: single value properties with list of values > 10)
* ''radiobutton'' (default for: single value properties with list of values <= 10)
|-
! {FORMAT}
| A format to be used to display the value. The following values are allowed:
* ''bullets'' (default)
* ''commas''
|}


==Semantic database==
The Option Property is implemented as a [[Special:Types/Text]] MediaWiki datatype.

The list of allowed values is defined on the property page using "Allows value" properties.


==Example==
<pre>
<concept name="Document">
  <structure>
    <property name="Approval status" multiplicity="one" editField="combobox"/>
  </structure>
</concept>

<properties>
  <property name="Approval status" type="Option" label="Approval status" attribute="status">
    <description>A text string to identify the approval status of an artefact.</description>
    <instruction/>
    <values default="Published">
      <value name="Under Development">Under Development</value>
      <value name="Published">Published</value>
      <value name="Endorsed">Endorsed</value>
      <value name="Approved">Approved</value>
      <value name="Superseded">Superseded</value>
      <value name="Unknown">Unknown</value>
    </values>
  </property>
</properties>
</pre>


==User Interface==
* '''View Page'''
The property displays a label associated with the selected value.

* '''Edit Page'''
The property provides a ComboBox input field to select a value.
The list of displayed values is controlled by the ''values'' element.

* '''Search Page'''
The property provides a ComboBox input field to select required search filter (including 'Not defined/Empty' value).
